    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001893_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><p><add hand="#U1" rend="gray"><hi rend="underline">Enclosure <choice><abbr>No</abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 6 in Letter <choice><abbr>No</abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 5 to <term type="occupation">Commander in Chief</term></hi>
<lb/><hi rend="underline black"><unclear cert="medium">Truebany</unclear></hi> <add hand="#U2" rend="large black"><persName>J. Wilson</persName></add>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><hi rend="underline black"><term type="occupation">Commander</term></hi></add></p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="7" unit="words"/><placeName><geogName type="river">River Shire</geogName></placeName> 
<lb/><space extent="7" unit="words"/><date when="1863-02-25">25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> February 1863</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Sir,</p>
<lb/><p>Three Black men who were brought
<lb/>from the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName> by the late <persName><term type="occupation">Bishop</term> <choice><orig>MacKenzie</orig><reg>Mackenzie</reg></choice></persName> to
<lb/>assist the <orgName>Universities' Mission</orgName> are now sent back
<lb/>to their homes - they were brought up the
<lb/>Courtesy of the <persName><term type="occupation">Admiral</term></persName> in a man of war, and
<lb/>if you can give them a passage down I am <w>au-
<lb break="no"/>thorized</w> by the <term type="occupation">Missionaries</term> to say that all expenses
<lb/>will cheerfully be paid to your <term type="occupation">Paymaster</term> by the
<lb/><term type="occupation">Bishop</term> of the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName>.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">In introducing them, it would scarcely be right in
<lb/>me not to mention that but little can be said in
<lb/>favour of their moral characters &amp; behaviour
<lb/>while with the <orgName>Mission</orgName>.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Allow me to add, that as the <placeName><geogName type="river">lower Shire</geogName></placeName>  
<lb/>has been completely depopulated by Slave-hunting -
<lb/>- drought, and famine, we can purchase no
<lb/>provisions for the "Pioneer" and will be
<lb/><space extent="8" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><hi rend="underline">obliged</hi></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><ab>The <term type="occupation">Captain</term> of any Man-of<supplied cert="high">-</supplied>War
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/>touching <unclear cert="low">at</unclear> <placeName><country><choice><orig>Mosambique</orig><reg>Mozambique</reg></choice></country></placeName></ab>
    
    <pb facs="liv_001893_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">obliged to return to the <placeName><geogName type="river">Kongone</geogName></placeName> - <placeName><settlement type="town"><choice><orig>Quilimane</orig><reg>Quelimane</reg></choice></settlement></placeName> or
<lb/><placeName><country>Mozambique</country></placeName> for Stores Sooner than we anticipated, 
<lb/>if you can leave any forces at either of these
<lb/>Ports you will confer a very great favour
<lb/>and render us essential Service; as it will
<lb/>be unwise for us to venture to <placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> at
<lb/>this Season in this Small Craft. <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>I have to
<lb/>beg very Earnestly that you will take this request
<lb/>into your favourable consideration.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>The <placeName><geogName type="river">Shire</geogName></placeName> has not risen as much
<lb/>as usual this Year, and we have found <w>con<choice><sic>=</sic><corr>-</corr></choice>
<lb break="no"/>siderable</w> difficulty in getting the two vessels
<lb/>up through the <placeName><geogName type="swamp"><term type="animal">Elephant</term> Swamp</geogName></placeName>, but we
<lb/>hope Soon to reach the <placeName><geogName type="cataract">Cataracts</geogName></placeName></p> <!-- I am not sure how to code "cataracts". JM -->
<lb/><p>Our <term type="occupation">Blacksmith</term> <persName>William Mcleod</persName> is
<lb/>obliged by <term type="ailment">disease of the Kidneys</term> to leave us -
<lb/>he is a very good man; - we got him from the 
<lb/>"Gorgon" on his passage to the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName>.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>I am <unclear cert="medium">&amp;c</unclear>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/>(<choice><abbr>sd</abbr><expan>signed</expan></choice>)<!-- There is a symbol here which I cannot make out. JM -->
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName>
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><hi rend="underline">H.M.S. Consul</hi></p>
    
            </div>
